item.title: Multivariable Calculus
item.description: aight, this is calc iii , the study of change but in 3D Let's see what your ass is gonna be lookin forward to: Main Topics Description 3D Functions take two inputs in and spit one output out, i.e. $\color{cyan} z = f(x,y)$ aka $\color{cyan} \mbb{R}^2 \to \mbb{R}$ 3D Derivatives $\Large \c{lime} \deriv{x}$ but in 3D, i.e. $\color{lime} \nabla f(x,y)$ 3D Integration volume!, i.e. $\Large \color{yellow} \iiint\limits_{R} dV$, so with this new tool we can finally answer the age old question of how fat yo mama truly is Vector Fields $ \color{orange} \mbb{R}^3 \to \mbb{R}^3$ functions, i.
